HEADWORD: Sorbition
<hw>Sor*bi"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sorbitio</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of drinking or sipping.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- sorbitol. A hexitol, C6H14O6, found in the mountain ash, now
produced by hydrogenation or electrolytic reduction of glucose. It has a
variet of uses, notably as a sugar substitute for diabetics, and to
improve the shelf-life of candy, as an osmotic agent, and as an
excipient in pharmaceutical preparations. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sorbonical</ent>⟦br⟧
